ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You know what you're getting yourself into if you've come this far! Just like research for credit, but double the hours. One advantage is that there is no research write-up required in the fall semester.Be prepared to spend a lot of time in lab. You might want to think about planning your course schedule to give yourself large, uninterrupted blocks of time for research. By the end of the term, I was averaging around 30 hours per week.
